meanings.definition: To exceed in raising or increasing.
meanings.sent1: She outraises her own expectations every time she practices.
meanings.sent2: The sun outraises the moon in brightness.
meanings.sent3: The little ant outraises the big elephant in carrying weight.
meanings.sent4: Her determination outraises any obstacle in her path.
meanings.sent5: The laughter of children outraises any sound in the playground.

meanings.definition: To surpass in raising funds or contributions.
meanings.sent1: He outraises his classmates in the school fundraiser every year.
meanings.sent2: The charity event outraises its donation goal every time.
meanings.sent3: The bake sale outraises the lemonade stand in profits.
meanings.sent4: Her persuasive speech outraises all other donation requests.
meanings.sent5: The community spirit outraises any monetary target set for the event.
